column12: Implant applicators and methods of administering implants
column13: Embodiments described herein relate generally to medical implant delivery apparatuses and methods. In some embodiments, an apparatus comprises a second cap, a needle hub at least partially disposed within the second cap, a pusher wire and a pusher wire connector disposed within the needle hub, a needle and a first cap. The second cap includes a proximal end, a distal end, and a longitudinal axis. The needle includes a first, beveled end configured to receive an implant, and a second end disposed within a hub pocket of the needle hub. The first cap is connected to the needle hub and disposed at a proximal end of the second cap. The pusher wire, the pusher wire connector, and the needle are substantially aligned with one another along the longitudinal axis of the second cap. In some embodiments, the pusher wire is sized to be received in the bore of the needle.

column13: 본 명세서에 기재된 실시예들은 일반적으로 의료 임플란트 전달 장치들 및 방법들에 관한 것이다. 몇몇 실시예들에서, 장치는 제 2 캡, 제 2 캡 내에 적어도 부분적으로 배치된 바늘 허브, 바늘 허브 내에 배치된 푸셔 와이어 및 푸셔 와이어 연결기, 바늘 및 제 1 캡을 포함한다. 제 2 캡은 근접 단부, 말단 단부, 및 길이방향 축을 포함한다. 바늘은 임플란트를 수용하도록 구성된 제 1 경사진 단부, 및 바늘 허브의 허브 포켓 내에 배치된 제 2 단부를 포함한다. 제 1 캡은 바늘 허브에 연결되고, 제 2 캡의 근접 단부에 배치된다. 푸셔 와이어, 푸셔 와이어 연결기, 및 바늘은 제 2 캡의 길이방향 축을 따라 서로 실질적으로 정렬된다. 몇몇 실시예들에서, 푸셔 와이어는 바늘의 보어에 수용되도록 하는 크기를 갖는다.

column13: System for the thermophysical caracterization of formulations and method for the preservation of Vibrio cholerae independently of the biotype, serotype or serogroup, intended to the preparation of oral vaccines. column12: CONSERVACIÓN DE FORMULACIONES VACUNALES DE VIBRIO CHOLERAE
column13: Conservación de formulaciones vacunales de Vibrio cholerae independientemente del biotipo, seropositivo o serogrupo, destinado a la elaboración de vacunas vivas orales. Incluye el empleo de formulaciones con proporciones adecuadas de al menos tres componentes representativos de los siguientes grupos: proteínas, péptidos, polímeros, leche descremada, glicina y solbitol, que garantizan que la temperatura de fusión incipiente de las mismas se sitúe por encima de -20sC. Se aseguran pérdidas de viabilidad inferiores a 0.7 orden logarítmico.

column12: CRISTALIZADOR DE PULMONES INTERCAMBIABLES O CASSETTE PARA MASAS COCIDAS
column13: El cristalizador cassette se aplica en la industria azucarera como complemento del proceso de cristalización de sacarosa iniciado en los tachos. La invención consiste en un nuevo diseno de cristalizador contínuo y abierto, constituido exteriormente por una envolvente en forma de U e interiormente por elementos de transferencia de calor conformados por pulmones dispuestos unos frente a los otros en posición vertical a lo largo del equipo, un tubo central al que van soldadas paletas reductoras y deflector o baffle entre zonas de enfriamiento y calentamiento. El fundamento de su construcción permite un alto grado de simplificación en el sistema de alimentación de agua fría y caliente. Además, la extracción de cualquiera de los pulmones tubulares o cassette, aún en plena operación permite la continuidad de la misma sin afectar el proceso. column12: Recovery of copper from ammoniacal copper sulfate solution
column13: Metallic copper is recovered from an ammoniacal copper sulfate solution by treating such solution with sulfur dioxide to form a precipitate of copper ammonium sulfite. The crystals are suspended in an acidic solution containing initially from 20 to 75 grams per liter of sulfuric acid, which preferably contains a substantial concentration (up to saturation) of ammonium sulfate, said solution containing from 40% to 70% by weight of such crystals, and the resulting suspension is heated at 140.degree.C. to 170.degree.C. and at 150 to 220 psi. until substantially all the copper ammonium sulfite has been converted to metallic copper. The metallic copper thereafter is separated from the residual solution.

column13: Die Erfindung geht aus von einer Kochfeldvorrichtung, insbesondere Induktionskochfeldvorrichtung, mit zumindest einer variablen Kochfläche (12), mit zumindest einer Bedienerschnittstelle (26) und mit zumindest einer Steuereinheit (28), welche bei zumindest einer Beheizungsart dazu vorgesehen ist, die Kochfläche (12) entlang wenigstens einer Unterteilungsrichtung in mehrere Heizzonen zu unterteilen, diesen ortsabhängig jeweils zumindest einen Heizparameter zu einer Beheizung zumindest eines auf der Heizzone aufgestellten Gargeschirrs (24) zuzuordnen und eine mit dem Heizparameter beheizte Kochzone (16, 34) zu bilden, welche dem Gargeschirr (24) zugeordnet ist. Um eine Sicherheit und eine Kosteneffizienz zu erhöhen, wird vorgeschlagen, dass die Steuereinheit (28) dazu vorgesehen ist, bei einer Anforderung der Beheizungsart für das Gargeschirr (24) zumindest eine Bedienhandlung eines Bedieners über die Bedienerschnittstelle (26) abzuwarten.

column12: FORMULACIONES PARA LIOFILIZACION DE VACUNAS VIVAS ATENUADAS DE VIBRIO CHOLERAE MEJORADAS EN SU SEGURIDAD AMBIENTAL
column13: La presente invencion provee formulaciones para la liofilizacion de vacunas vivas atenuadas de vibrio cholerae mejoradas en su seguridad ambiental, que comprende en su composicion, combinaciones de al menos tres de las siguientes sustancias:lactosa, peptona, extracto de levadura y sorbitol. Dichas formulaciones garantizan solubilidad instantAnea y buenas características organolÉpticas de la preparacion vacunal, cierta tolerancia del agente vacunal a la humedad y a la presencia transitoria de oxígeno en el envase y la estabilidad del producto sin necesidad de almacenamiento a temperaturas de congelacion.

column12: SHORT-CIRCUITING DEVICE FOR SECONDARY NETWORKS.
column13: The present invention is related to a device for grounding and short-circuiting secondary networks for supplying electric power, the same consisting in a metal conducting column with clamps arranged at the same distance of the secondary network conductors, the clamps being closed by the mechanical action of a lever and camshaft in order to press the conductors and establish a physical and electrical connection point in common with regard to the neutral electric conductor. The purpose of the invention is to ensure the function of short-circuiting the lines for conducting electric power resulting from the supplying transformer so as to work safely at the moment of performing a preventive or corrective maintenance over the components of the low voltage network, thus reducing the risk of an electric discharge caused by a possible current return upon connecting an alternate power generating source to the supplying network through the connection of a final user.

column12: METHOD AND DEVICE FOR INSPECTING LINEAR INFRASTRUCTURES
column13: The invention relates to a method and to the corresponding devices therefor, which is used automatically or manually to inspect linear infrastructures such as power lines and which is controlled by a single operator. column12: METHOD FOR A HOTPLATE
column13: Die Erfindung geht aus von einem Verfahren für ein Kochfeld (10a-c), insbesondere zu einer Herstellung und/oder zu einem Betrieb des Kochfelds (10a-c), welches zumindest eine Bedienerschnittstelle (12a-c) aufweist und welches in wenigstens einem Betriebszustand, in welchem für eine Beheizung eines Gargeschirrs (14a-c) mit zumindest einer vorliegenden Beheizungsart lediglich eine Heizleistung von maximal einem Heizleistungsgrenzwert zur Verfügung steht, welcher kleiner ist als eine in wenigstens einem weiteren Betriebszustand für die vorliegende Beheizungsart auswählbare Heizleistung, ein Überschreiten des Heizleistungsgrenzwerts verhindert. Um eine gattungsgemäße Vorrichtung mit verbesserten Eigenschaften hinsichtlich einer Flexibilität bereitzustellen, wird vorgeschlagen, dass das Überschreiten des Heizleistungsgrenzwerts durch Anpassung der Bedienerschnittstelle (12a-c) in Abhängigkeit von der vorliegenden Beheizungsart verhindert wird.

column12: METHOD AND DEVICE FOR INSPECTING LINEAR INFRASTRUCTURES
column13: It consists of a method and the respective devices for the automatic or manual inspection of linear infrastructures, such as electric lines, which is controlled by a single operator. The system is divided mainly into two stages, the on-board stage on the mobile means and the subsequent post-processing stage in which the final report is issued. The on-board equipment consists of two gyrostabilised platforms (1) and (2), one of which (1) is responsible for collecting panoramic images that will provide general information on the lines, and the other (2) has the function of capturing detailed images automatically. <IMAGE>

column12: METHOD FOR PROGNOSTICATING STROKE
column13: The present invention relates to a method for prognosticating functional progress in a stroke patient, which includes determining the Arg72Pro polymorphism of the Tp53 gene in a biological sample of said patient, where the presence of the Arg/Arg genotype is associated with a bad functional prognosis of the stroke and the presence of the Pro/Arg genotype or the Prb/Pro genotype indicates a good functional prognosis of the stroke.

column12: METHOD FOR FORMING BLANKS AND PRESS FOR PERFORMING THE METHOD
column13: FIELD: plastic metal working. SUBSTANCE: forming press includes group of lower dies having stationary die and movable die turned to stationary die and spaced from it by some distance along axis of press and restricting volume for blank; and outer circumferential wall. Movable die has zone of basic level laying in plane of blank normal relative to axis of press and three rotatable symmetrical sectors raised over zone of basic level. Each sector is angular sector of disc and it is arranged at angular shift relative to other sectors. Mechanism of press includes axial drive for moving movable die in direction parallel relative to press axis and also drive for periodic circular feed for rotating movable die around axis of press by angle of periodical circular feed. At operation axial drive performs reciprocation motion, drive for periodical circular feed rotates die by angle less than sector angle while axial drive performs another stroke. At repeating such steps cyclic forming of the whole blank is realized. EFFECT: possibility for forming blank at nominal effort less than that during standard forming process. 17 cl, 11 dwg

column12: TRANSCRIPTIONAL FUSION VECTORS FOR UNI AND BIDIRECTIONAL PROMOTER REGIONS FOR USE IN LACTIC BACTERIA
column13: The invention relates to a recombinant nucleotide sequence that includes the sequence of the mrfp gene that codes for a red autofluorescent protein optimized for expression in lactic bacteria, as well as the vectors that comprise same. The invention likewise relates to the cells that include the sequence or the vector of the invention and the uses thereof. In addition, the invention relates to the use of both the sequence and the vector for the detection and characterization of a unidirectional or bidirectional promoter region, as well as to the use thereof for transcription. The invention further relates to the use of cells that contain the sequence or vector of the invention, for determining the colonizing ability of cells. The invention also relates to the methods associated with the uses of the invention, to a kit that includes the elements of the invention and to the use thereof.

column12: Vibrio cholerae with improved biological safety features in freeze dried form
column13: The present invention discloses new live attenuated strains for oral immunization against cholera that are provided in freeze dried formulations for long term storage and administration to humans. These strains combine the two most important properties of live attenuated cholera vaccine candidates. One such property is being well tolerated by people ingesting them. This was achieved by virtue of mutations already described in the art. The second property is having enhanced environmental safety due to the absence of VGJΦ DNA in their genomes and also due to null mutations in the mshA gene or other spontaneous mutations conducive to the lack of MSHA type IV fimbria on the bacterial surface. This was done envisioning that VGJΦ is a filamentous phage able to recombine with CTXΦ and disseminate the cholera toxin genes. This VGJΦ phage as well as the VGJΦ-CTXΦ recombinants uses the MSHA fibers as receptor. Being devoid of MSHA fimbria the vaccine candidates are protected from acquiring CTXΦ from the recombinant hybrid VGJΦ-CTXΦ. Being devoid of VGJΦ, the vaccine candidates are impaired in the dissemination of CTXΦ, via VGJΦ.

column12: ATTENUATED STRAINS OF VIBRIO CHOLERAE AND LYOPHILISED VACCINES CONTAINING SAME
column13: The invention relates to novel live strains which are intended for oral immunisation against cholera and which are lyophilised in formulations enabling the long-term storage thereof. The aforementioned strains combine the two most important properties that known vaccine candidates must have for the purpose of oral immunisation against cholera, namely: a level of reactogenicity which is reduced to acceptable levels through the use of known mutations which have been described in prior art; and an improved environmental safety index owing to the suppression of the mshA gene or spontaneous mutations which result in the absence of the MSHA pilus on the outer surface of the bacteria and the absence of the VGJF phage in the gene pool thereof, which, if present, enable the incorporation and dissemination of the CTXF phage assisted by VGJF.

column12: Attenuated strains of vibrio cholerae with improved biological safety features in freeze dried form for oral vaccination
column13: The present invention discloses new live attenuated strains for oral immunization against cholera that are provided in freeze dried formulations for long term storage and administration to humans. These strains combine the two most important properties of live attenuated cholera vaccine candidates. One such property is being well tolerated by people ingesting them. This was achieved by virtue of mutations already described in the art. The second property is having enhanced environmental safety due to the absence of VGJΦ DNA in their genomes and also due to null mutations in the mshA gene or other spontaneous mutations conducive to the lack of MSHA type IV fimbria on the bacterial surface. This was done envisioning that VGJΦ is a filamentous phage able to recombine with CTXΦ and disseminate the cholera toxin genes. This VGJΦ phage as well as the VGJΦ-CTXΦ recombinants uses the MSHA fibers as receptor. Being devoid of MSHA fimbria the vaccine candidates are protected from acquiring CTXΦ from the recombinant hybrid VGJΦ-CTXΦ. Being devoid of VGJΦ, the vaccine candidates are impaired in the dissemination of CTXΦ, via VGJΦ.

column12: CEPAS ATENUADAS DE VIBRIO CHOLERAE Y VACUNAS LIOFILIZADAS QUE LAS CONTIENEN.
column13: La presente invención propone nuevas cepas vivas para inmunizar oralmente contra el cólera, liofilizadas en formulaciones que permiten su almacenamiento a largo plazo. En estas cepas se combinan las dos propiedades más importantes que deben poseer los candidatos vacunales concebidos para inmunizar contra el cólera. Una de estas propiedades es la de poseer un nivel de reactogenicidad disminuido hasta niveles aceptables, en virtud del empleo de mutaciones ya conocidas y descritas en el arte anterior. La otra propiedad es poseer un mejor índice de seguridad ambiental en virtud de la supresión del gen mshA o mutaciones espontáneas que conduzcan a la ausencia de la fimbria MSHA en la superficie externa de la bacteria y la ausencia del fago VGJF en su dotación genética, los cuales, si estuvieran presentes, permitirían la incorporación y diseminación del fago CTXF asistida por VGJF, objeto de la presente invención.

column12: ATTENUATED STRAINS OF VIBRIO CHOLERAE WITH IMPROVED BIOLOGICAL SAFETY FEATURES IN FREEZE DRIED FORM FOR ORAL VACCINATION
column13: THE PRESENT INVENTION DISCLOSES NEW LIVE ATTENUATED STRAINS FOR ORAL IMMUNIZATION AGAINST CHOLERA THAT ARE PROVIDED IN FREEZE DRIED FORMULATIONS FOR LONG TERM STORAGE AND ADMINISTRATION TO HUMANS. THESE STRAINS COMBINE THE TWO MOST IMPORTANT PROPERTIES OF LIVE ATTENUATED CHOLERA VACCINE CANDIDATES. ONE SUCH PROPERTY IS BEING WELL TOLERATED BY PEOPLE INGESTING THEM. THIS WAS ACHIEVED BY VIRTUE OF MUTATIONS ALREADY DESCRIBED IN THE ART. THE SECOND PROPERTY IS HAVING ENHANCED ENVIRONMENTAL SAFETY DUE TO THE ABSENCE OF VGJ DNA IN THEIR GENOMES AND ALSO DUE TO NULL MUTATIONS IN THE MSHA GENE OR OTHER SPONTANEOUS MUTATIONS CONDUCIVE TO THE LACK OF MSHA TYPE IV FIMBRIA ON THE BACTERIAL SURFACE. THIS WAS DONE ENVISIONING THAT VGJ IS A FILAMENTOUS PHAGE ABLE TO RECOMBINE WITH CTX AND DISSEMINATE THE CHOLERA TOXIN GENES. THIS VGJ PHAGE AS WELL AS THE VGJ-CTX RECOMBINANTS USES THE MSHA FIBERS AS RECEPTOR. BEING DEVOID OF MSHA FIMBRIA THE VACCINE CANDIDATES ARE PROTECTED FROM ACQUIRING CTX FROM THE RECOMBINANT HYBRID VGJ-CTX. BEING DEVOID OF VGJ, THE VACCINE CANDIDATES ARE IMPAIRED IN THE DISSEMINATION OF CTX, VIA VGJ.
